All open world terrain, you can drive basically where ever you want, but I think that a little bit bigger world will help with some more variety in the terrain itself. The graphics are great! like the driving physics, and certain vehicles are paired up with others to get the job done. decent levels, but some of them just over lap on submissions. For ex. I went to the builders merchant to pick up some stuff, bring it back, then the next mission, I have to go back then and do the same thing. this may happen 2-4 times per 'tender' a glitch I think I found is that somehow the down function on some vehicles like the forklift sometimes gets glitched so I can't move it down. but other than that, I think it was the best $3.92 I've spent in December! great game, and thanks Devs!

The cameras are not that great when working with the crane. And the load truck w. crane is rather buggy. The loads don't stay in place once you set them on the truck. They just vibrate off, before you finish. This leads to an endless cycle of pick & drop. This may be realistic, but not the best modeled. The only work around is to ignore the tutorial advice and leave the side panels up.  Beyond these issues, the game is fun. As I get use to the controls, I save time. I'm grateful the developers don't add pressure allowing equipment damage. I can play at my own pace. That may change as I get deeper in the game, but for now, I can play missions and enjoy the vehicles I bought.   Yes, I did use the IAP to buy all the vehicles. Don't usually do that, but IMHO the $10 extra bucks didn't feel like a sham.
